-- Brazil's Itau bank to consider $6.4 bln capital increase
-- By Luciana Bruno
-- Thu Mar 20, 2014 07:55PM EDT
-- None



RIO DE JANEIRO, March 20 (Reuters) - Itaú Unibanco Holding SA <ITUB4.SA>, Brazil's largest private bank by market value, called a shareholders meeting for April 23 to consider a 15 billion reais ($6.4 billion) capital increase, according to a securities filing on Thursday.

Under the plan, Itaú would issue 502.8 million shares at the rate of one new share for every 10 held, the filing said. Of the 502.8 million shares, 251.8 would be common shares and 250.9 million preferred shares.